1. power on
2. Press Esc to boot menu
3. scroll down and select something like "advanced setup"
4. new window shows list of os to boot from. select "latest os in recover mode"
5. new window shows series of options. select "root", press enter when it prompts for maintainance
6. you will be in root bash. type "ls /home" shows all users
7. execute "passwd username" to change password. pwd will be changed. do restart and use new pwd to login
